Project Title :

Future Sales prediction of an online computer hardware company

Problem Statement:

The company plans to increase their sales for the upcoming year. They have gathered their sales data of past 3 years which contains information reagrding customer purchase history like name, state, product name, product category, product cost, sales, quantity, total cost and total sales. By utilising the data, they want to increase the sales eventaully maximise the profit by reducing the costs.

The machine learning task includes applying regression tasks to the provided data and train suitable models. Finally the model with best accuracy will be selected and the best model will be checked by visualising.

Oulier Analysis

In[11]:
acols = ['Cost', 'Sales', 'Quantity', 'Total_Cost', 'Total_Sales']

mt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sa.boxplot(data=sales_df[acols])
mt.title('Boxplot of Numeric Columns')
mt.xlabel('Columns')
mt.ylabel('Values')
mt.show()

We can see that there are some outliers. so we have to remove this outlier by using winsorizer method.

In[12]:
winso = Wins(tail='both', capping_method='iqr', fold=1.5, variables=acols)

winso.fit(sales_df)

sales_df = winso.transform(sales_df)
In[13]:
mt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sa.boxplot(data=sales_df[acols])
mt.title('Boxplot of Numeric Columns')

After using winsorizer method outlires has been removed.

Removing column with nominal values

In[14]:
columns = ['Order_Number', 'Customer_Name', 'Order_Date']
sales_df.drop(columns, axis=1, inplace=True)
In[15]:
columns = ['State_Code', 'Status', 'Product', 'Category', 'Brand', 'Cost', 'Sales', 'Quantity', 'Total_Cost', 'Assigned Supervisor']
variable = 'Total_Sales'

v = sales_df[columns]
c = sales_df[variable]

Division of data

In[16]:
v_train, v_test, c_train, c_test = tts(v, c,  random_state=42, test_size=0.2)
In[17]:
acols = ['Cost', 'Sales', 'Quantity', 'Total_Cost']
ctg = ['State_Code', 'Status', 'Product', 'Category', 'Brand', 'Assigned Supervisor']

nt = StandardScaler()
cc = OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore')

Transfer = CT(transformers=[ ('num', nt, acols), ('cat', cc, ctg)])

v_train = Transfer.fit_transform(v_train)
v_test = Transfer.transform(v_test)

Ditecting Accuracy

In[23]:
y_pr_lin = linreg_model.predict(v_test)
r2_li_re = sc(c_test, y_pr_lin)
print(" Linear Regression R-squared score:", r2_li_re)

y_p_r = gs.best_estimator_.predict(v_test)
r2_r = sc(c_test, y_p_r)
print("R2 Score for Random Forest:", r2_r)

y_pr_gb = gsg.best_estimator_.predict(v_test)
r2_gb = sc(c_test, y_pr_gb)
print("R2 Score for Gradient Boosting:", r2_gb)

y_pr_svm = gsg.best_estimator_.predict(v_test)
r2_svm = sc(c_test, y_pr_svm)
print("R2 Score for Support Vector Machine:", r2_svm)

 Linear Regression R-squared score: 0.9999999999650392
R2 Score for Random Forest: 1.0
R2 Score for Gradient Boosting: 0.9958638543338796
R2 Score for Support Vector Machine: 0.9958638543338796

Here we have firstly trained and tested the model then used various machine learning algorithm and find R2 square of each algorithm .

Checking the best model

In[24]:
R = {'Linear Regression': r2_li_re,'Random Forest': r2_r,'Gradient Boosting': r2_gb,'Support Vector Machine': r2_svm}

best_model = max(R, key=R.get)
print(f'The best model is: {best_model} with an R2 score of {R[best_model]}')

The best model is: Random Forest with an R2 score of 1.0

From the above results we have calculated and compaired the various algorithms and found random forest as a best model.

In[25]:
mt.figure(figsize=(11, 7))
mt.scatter(c_test, y_p_r, label='Random Forest', color='green')
mt.plot([min(c_test), max(c_test)], [min(c_test), max(c_test)], '--', color='red')
mt.xlabel('Existing Total_Sales')
mt.ylabel('Speculated Total_Sales')
mt.title('Existing vs Speculated Total_Sales')
mt.show()

From above graph we have calculated actual as well as predicted total sales. These plot tells us that the trained model has great predicting accuracy and hence it can be used for predicting future sales.

Conclusion

In the above charts and graphs we can observe that Random Forest has the best accuracy of 1. we can also observe that total sales is more than total cost therefore the bussiness is running in a good position.
